main event: An object, silver in color, elliptical in shape, 3-4 inches in diameter, looked like a satellite moving at a slow speed from about 45 degrees elevation to 180 degrees azimuth in 5 seconds.
interesting points: The object was observed for a duration of 5 minutes.
The object moved from west-northwest to east-southeast.
The report states that the observation was likely a meteor.
The observer could not track the object long enough to gather sufficient data for evaluation.
The report includes details about the size, shape, and movement of the observed object.
sighted object: Silver, elliptical object resembling a satellite
